    "body": "Given the way fast and snap sync work, it may make sense to not start sync at all if peers are advertising a total difficulty in excess of TTD until the CL client sends the first `forkChoiceUpdated` notification which would identify the chain to sync.  If you sync'd the TTD block you'd likely download a very old world state and then either have to full sync from there or discard it and start a new fast/snap sync from where the CL starts from.\r\n\r\nIf the CL is doing a full sync of the beacon chain, that first notice will be for the TTD block  and the CL would then execute each block past that, but when the CL is using checkpoint sync it's starting sync will be close to the chain head which may be very significantly past the TTD block and the CL will not execute any blocks prior to the checkpoint state it starts with.",
